        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 1:55PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 155 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm west
of Gloverville, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Walterboro, Cottageville, Round O, Canadys, Sidney, Hiotts,
Lowcountry Regional Airport, Colleton Medical Center, Thayer and
Gloverville.

This includes I-95 in South Carolina between mile markers 57 and 68.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
